Dear all,
We are excited to announce a new course: Spatial Proteomics Data Analysis in R/Bioconductor: From Mass Spectrometry to Subcellular Maps
 
Dates: Online, 10?12 November 


 
Course website: [ https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/spatial-proteomics-in-r/ ]( https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/spatial-proteomics-in-r/ ) 
 
 
This hands-on course introduces the analysis of MS-based subcellular spatial proteomics data, focusing on how to transform mass spectrometry outputs into meaningful subcellular protein localisation maps using R/Bioconductor.
 
Across three days (12:00?16:00 Berlin time), participants will learn how to build reproducible workflows in R for:
 
- Data import, processing, filtering, and normalisation using Bioconductor (QFeatures)
- Exploratory data analysis, visualisation, and clustering
- Protein annotation and quality control of spatial proteomics data
- Machine learning approaches for protein localisation prediction
- Generation of high-confidence subcellular protein maps
 
This course is aimed at proteomics researchers, bioinformaticians, and data analysts interested in gaining practical experience with MS-based spatial proteomics data. 
 
