Dear all,
We are pleased to announce the online course ?Reproducibility Data Analysis with R?, taking place 8?11 June.
 
Course website: [ https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/r-reproducibility/ ]( https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/r-reproducibility/ ) 
 
Reproducibility is a cornerstone of reliable science, yet many analyses remain difficult to reproduce due to missing dependencies, unclear workflows, or poor documentation. This course provides practical, hands-on training to help you build fully reproducible and transparent data analysis workflows in R.
 
Participants will learn how to structure projects effectively, manage dependencies, and share analyses in a robust and sustainable way using widely adopted tools such as Quarto, Git/GitHub, renv, and Docker. The course also introduces research compendia as a best-practice framework for organising computational research.
 
By the end of the course, you will be able to design and implement complete reproducible workflows?from project setup to version-controlled and containerised analyses?ready for collaboration and long-term reuse.
 
The course is aimed at researchers and data scientists with basic experience in R who want to improve the transparency, reliability, and shareability of their work.
 
 
 
